        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 30 at 2:01PM PDT by NWS Medford OR</headline>
        <description>At 201 PM PDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 10
miles east of Nordheimer Campground, or 19 miles east of Orleans,
moving west at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Nordheimer Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
